msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Update Changelog\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "        ./release NEW_VERSION PREVIOUS_RELEASED_TAG\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "        ./release 0.3 0.2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This populates the Changelog with the Git log entries, then launches an "
"editor for the needed cleanup of the result."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Build images\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Carefully read the build logs to make sure nothing bad happened."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#, no-wrap
msgid "SquashFS files order\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Build ISO images, profile them and update `squashfs.order` in the Git "
"repository. See [[todo/improve_boot_time_on_cd]] for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Until [[todo/automated_tests]] are setup, some minimal, manual testing has "
"to be done by the person doing the release, in addition to the real-world "
"tests done by fellow beta-testers:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "iceweasel: is web browsing really torified?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "pidgin: is an IRC session really torified?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "firewall: is the Tor-enforcement effective?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"local partitions: are any local hard-disk partitions mounted or used as "
"swap?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"icedove: check that the profile works, is updated, and torified "
"(specifically the EHLO/HELO SMTP messages it sends, see [an or-talk thread "
"about it](http://archives.seul.org/or/talk/Aug-2008/msg00261.html))."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Generate the Torrents\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"First, create a directory with a suitable name for every built image to be "
"released, such as `amnesia-i386-gnome-fr-0.3-20091126-cd`; note that"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "the ISO image's Torrent directory must end with `-cd`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "the USB image's Torrent directory must end with `-usb`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Second, copy the built images to these brand new directories."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Third, generate detached GnuPG signatures for every published image, in the "
"same directory as the image; e.g."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    gpg --armor --default-key F93E735F \\\n"
"        --detach-sign amnesia-i386-gnome-fr-0.3-20091126.iso\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Fourth, create a `.torrent` file for every directory to be published:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    mktorrent -a \\\n"
"      "
"'https://www.les-renseignements-genereux.org/tracker/announce,http://z6gw6skubmo2pj43.onion:8080/announce' "
"\\\n"
"      <DIRECTORY>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Fifth, check the generated `.torrent` files metainfo, e.g.  using "
"`btshowmetainfo`, to make sure they don't contain unwanted information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Announce, seed and test the Torrents\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Announce and seed the Torrents using whatever box you can.  A decent, stable "
"and permanent Internet connexion is required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Test them with a BitTorrent client running in a different place."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Update the website and Git repository\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Add the `.torrent` and `.packages` files to the Git repository's "
"`wiki/src/torrents/files/` directory. There, update the symlinks (with "
"persistent names) to the new `.torrent` and `.packages` files (FIXME: dev "
"releases and/or latest tagged stable release?)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Write the announce for the release in `news/version_X.Y.mdwn`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Then add the updated `debian/changelog` and you should be ready to record "
"the last commit before tagging happens:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    git commit -m \"releasing version ${NEW_VERSION}\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tag the release in Git\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    git tag -u F93E735F -m \"tagging version ${NEW_VERSION}\" "
"\"${NEW_VERSION}\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Go wild!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Push the last commits and the release tag to our Git repository:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    git push --tags\n"
msgstr ""
